# Admin UI Package Guidelines

The Admin UI package provides a web interface for managing error codes and translations.

## Structure

- [packages/admin-ui/src/components](mdc:packages/admin-ui/src/components) - React components
- [packages/admin-ui/src/pages](mdc:packages/admin-ui/src/pages) - Page components
- [packages/admin-ui/src/services](mdc:packages/admin-ui/src/services) - API integration

## Component Design

- Use functional components with hooks
- Reuse components from the shared-ui package
- Follow a consistent naming convention
- Create small, focused components

## State Management

- Use React context for global state
- Keep component state local when possible
- Use React Query for API data fetching
- Handle loading and error states properly

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include ARIA attributes where necessary
- Ensure keyboard navigation works properly
- Test with screen readers and other assistive technologies

## Internationalization

- Support multiple languages in the Admin UI itself
- Use a consistent i18n solution
- Avoid hardcoded text strings
- Handle right-to-left languages when applicable
